      • processMessageInput

        void processMessageInput(String XMLrequest,
                       int requestSize,
                       String url,
                       String soapAction,
                       String HttpUsername,
                       String HashCode,
                       HashMap headers,
                       String ipaddress,
                       String agentclassname,
                       String relatedtransaction,
                       String threadid)
        caches stored data and adds it to the message map. see note on agentclassname reference
        Parameters:
        XMLrequest - - may be null, the request content
        requestSize - - size of the payload
        url - - the requested URL that the client asked for http://localhost/path
        soapAction - - SOAPAction or HTTP Method
        HttpUsername - the username or DN of the requestor
        HashCode - - very important, a unique identifier for this message. Use UUID.random
        headers - - Transport layer headers of the request
        ipaddress - - IP of the requestor
        agentclassname - - the class of the agent that recorded the message. MUST CONTAIN "client" IF THIS IS A CLIENT or from a proxy TRANSACTION!! this is necessary for proper URL resolution
        relatedtransaction - - if this transaction was also recorded elsewhere, pull this data from the http headers
        threadid - - if this transaction was also recorded elsewhere, pull this data from the http headers. or generate a new one if it was not present using UUID.random
